OL,3,CJersey emissions drop by nearly 50%
OL,4,Csince 1990
OL,6,Fgreenhouse emissions dropped by 47%
OL,7,Fbetween 1990 and 2022.
OL,9,FNew statistics show is still the area
OL,10,Fthat produces the most, although this
OL,11,Ffigure has dropped by more than a
OL,12,Ffifth in that period.
OL,14,FThe overall reduction in emissions is
OL,15,Fmainly due to the island's energy
OL,16,Fsector becoming greener - 31% came of
OL,17,FJersey's carbon output from it in 1990
OL,18,Fcompared with just 8% in 2022.
